{"id":"amoz","term":"Amoz","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Strong, the father of the prophet Isaiah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 19:2\">2 Kings 19:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:20\">20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 20:1\">20:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:1\">Isa. 1:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 2:1\">2:1</a>). As to his personal history little is positively known. He is supposed by some to have been the “man of God” spoken of in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 25:7\">2 Chr. 25:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 25:8\">8</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Kings 19:2","Genesis 1:20","Genesis 20:1","Isaiah 1:1","Isaiah 2:1","2 Chronicles 25:7","2 Chronicles 25:8"]}